{"title_page": "Trichophyton interdigitale", "text_new": "{{Taxobox\n| image = Trichophyton mentagrophytes (257 18) Cultured.jpg\n| image_caption = ''Trichophyton mentagrophytes''\n| regnum = [[Fungus|Fungi]]\n| divisio = [[Ascomycota]]\n| classis = [[Eurotiomycetes]]\n| ordo = [[Onygenales]]\n| familia = [[Arthrodermataceae]]\n| genus = ''[[Trichophyton]]''\n| species = '''''T. interdigitale'''''\n| binomial = ''Trichophyton interdigitale''\n| binomial_authority = [[Henry Priestly|Priestley]] (1917)\n}}\n[[File:Trichophyton mentagrophytes (257 19) From a microculture and an infected hair.jpg|thumb|''Trichophyton mentagrophytes'' on a hair]]\n'''''Trichophyton interdigitale''''' is a clonal line within sexual species ''[[Trichophyton mentagrophytes|T. mentagrophytes]]''.<ref name=deHoog2017/> It causes [[onychomycosis]] and [[tinea pedis]] in humans, and has been never isolated from animals. ''Trichophyton interdigitale'' isolates cannot be reliably discriminated from ''T.{{spaces|1|nb}}mentagrophytes'' by cultural techniques or [[Matrix-assisted laser desorption/ionization|MALDI-TOF]] mass spectrometry and therefore [[Internal transcribed spacer|ITS region]] DNA sequencing is recommended.<ref name=Pchelin2019/>\n\n==Critics==\n''Trichophyton interdigitale'' is defined by its capability of transmission between human hosts and clonal way of reproduction. However, there is at least one another anthropophilic clonal line within ''[[Trichophyton mentagrophytes|T. mentagrophytes]]'', phylogenetically unrelated to ''T. interdigitale''.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=deHoog2017>{{Cite journal |vauthors=de Hoog GS, Dukik K, Monod M, et al. |year=2017 |title=Toward a novel multilocus phylogenetic taxonomy for the dermatophytes |journal=[[Mycopathologia]] |volume=182 |issue=1-2 |pages=5\u201331 |doi=10.1007/s11046-016-0073-9 |pmid=27783317}}</ref>\n<ref name=Pchelin2019>{{cite journal  |vauthors=Pchelin IM, Azarov DV, Churina MA, etal |title=Species boundaries in the Trichophyton mentagrophytes / T. interdigitale species complex |journal=[[Medical Mycology]] |volume=57 |issue=6 |pages=781\u20139 |year=2019 |pmid=30462248 |doi=10.1093/mmy/myy115}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n{{Mycoses}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q7840903}}\n\n[[Category:Onygenales]]\n[[Category:Fungi described in 1917]]\n\n\n{{Eurotiomycetes-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Taxobox\n| image = Trichophyton mentagrophytes (257 18) Cultured.jpg\n| image_caption = ''Trichophyton mentagrophytes''\n| regnum = [[Fungus|Fungi]]\n| divisio = [[Ascomycota]]\n| classis = [[Eurotiomycetes]]\n| ordo = [[Onygenales]]\n| familia = [[Arthrodermataceae]]\n| genus = ''[[Trichophyton]]''\n| species = '''''T. interdigitale'''''\n| binomial = ''Trichophyton interdigitale''\n| binomial_authority = [[Henry Priestly|Priestley]] (1917)\n}}\n[[File:Trichophyton mentagrophytes (257 19) From a microculture and an infected hair.jpg|thumb|''Trichophyton mentagrophytes'' on a hair]]\n'''''Trichophyton interdigitale''''' is a clonal line within sexual species ''[[Trichophyton mentagrophytes|T. mentagrophytes]]''.<ref name=deHoog2017/> It causes [[onychomycosis]] and [[tinea pedis]] in humans, and has been never isolated from animals. ''Trichophyton interdigitale'' isolates cannot be reliably discriminated from ''T. mentagrophytes'' by cultural techniques or [[Matrix-assisted laser desorption/ionization|MALDI-TOF]] mass spectrometry and therefore [[Internal transcribed spacer|ITS region]] DNA sequencing is recommended.<ref name=Pchelin2019/>\n\n==Critics==\n''Trichophyton interdigitale'' is defined by its capability of transmission between human hosts and clonal way of reproduction. However, there is at least one another anthropophilic clonal line within ''[[Trichophyton mentagrophytes|T. mentagrophytes]]'', phylogenetically unrelated to ''T. interdigitale''.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=deHoog2017>{{Cite journal |vauthors=de Hoog GS, Dukik K, Monod M, et al. |year=2017 |title=Toward a novel multilocus phylogenetic taxonomy for the dermatophytes |journal=[[Mycopathologia]] |volume=182 |issue=1-2 |pages=5\u201331 |doi=10.1007/s11046-016-0073-9 |pmid=27783317}}</ref>\n<ref name=Pchelin2019>{{cite journal  |vauthors=Pchelin IM, Azarov DV, Churina MA, etal |title=Species boundaries in the Trichophyton mentagrophytes / T. interdigitale species complex |journal=[[Medical Mycology]] |volume=57 |issue=6 |pages=781\u20139 |year=2019 |pmid=30462248 |doi=10.1093/mmy/myy115}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n{{Mycoses}}\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q7840903}}\n\n[[Category:Onygenales]]\n[[Category:Fungi described in 1917]]\n\n\n{{Eurotiomycetes-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ivan Pchelin", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trichophyton_interdigitale"}
